Note: can also create a .gvimrc for gvim config settings; symlink similarly

Installation: Create symlinks:
    
    ln -s ~/config/.vim ~/.vim
    ln -s ~/config/.vimrc ~/.vimrc

Adding non-plugin stuff: (in .vim directory)

    git add .
    git commit -m "description"
    git push

Getting latest version: (in .vim directory)

    git pull

Adding plugins:

    git submodule add <address of plugin on github> ~/config/.vim/bundle/<plugin name>
    then steps below this

Pulling plugins: (in .vim directory)

    git submodule init
    git submodule update

    or, try git submodule foreach git pull

Getting rid of plugins:

    http://chrisjean.com/2009/04/20/git-submodules-adding-using-removing-and-updating/
    git rm --cached <path of plugin>, e.g. bundle<plugin name>
